<i>adverb</i>: 환히 [환ː히], 차곡차곡 [차곡차곡], 쭈르르 [쭈르르], 쪼르르 [쪼르르], 주르르 [주르르], 조촐히 [조촐히], 조르르 [조르르], 정연히 [정연히], 정결히 [정결히], 정갈히 [정갈히], 얌전히 [얌전히], 시원히 [시원히], 시원스레 [시원스레], 반듯반듯 [반듣빤듣], 말짱히 [말짱히], 또박또박 [또박또박], 단정히 [단정히], 깨끗이 [깨끄시] <br>
<ul style="list-style-type:square">
<li><i>adverb</i><br>
<dt>환히 [환ː히]</dt><br>
<dd>1. brightly; radiantly</dd><br>
<dd>빛이 비치어 맑고 밝게.</dd><br>
<dd>In the state of being very clear and bright as light shines.</dd><br>
<dd>2. openly; clearly</dd><br>
<dd>앞이 탁 트여 넓고 시원스럽게.</dd><br>
<dd>In the state of something imparting a feeling of not being confined, because it has an open view.</dd><br>
<dd>3. clearly; obviously</dd><br>
<dd>무슨 일이 되어 가는 사정이나 속내가 분명하게.</dd><br>
<dd>In the manner of the progress or intention of a certain event being clear.</dd><br>
<dd>4. attractively; finely; neatly</dd><br>
<dd>얼굴이 깔끔하게 잘생겨 보기에 좋게.</dd><br>
<dd>In the state of having a pleasing, neat, and attractive appearance.</dd><br>
<dd>5. brightly; beamingly; radiantly</dd><br>
<dd>표정이나 성격이 명랑하고 밝게.</dd><br>
<dd>In the state of one's face or personality being bright and cheerful.</dd><br>
<dt>차곡차곡 [차곡차곡]</dt><br>
<dd>1. neatly</dd><br>
<dd>물건을 가지런하게 겹쳐 쌓거나 포개 놓은 모양.</dd><br>
<dd>In the manner of objects being stacked or piled in a neat pile.</dd><br>
<dd>2. in a calm and orderly way</dd><br>
<dd>말이나 행동 등을 천천히 순서에 따라 조리 있게 하는 모양.</dd><br>
<dd>In the manner of speaking, acting, etc., in a slow, orderly and coherent way.</dd><br>
<dt>쭈르르 [쭈르르]</dt><br>
<dd>1. quickly; in a trickle</dd><br>
<dd>굵은 물줄기 등이 빠르게 흘러내리는 소리. 또는 그 모양.</dd><br>
<dd>A word used to describe the sound made when a thick flow of water runs down, or such a motion.</dd><br>
<dd>2. quickly; in a sliding manner</dd><br>
<dd>사람이나 물건 등이 기울어진 곳에서 빠르게 미끄러져 내리는 모양.</dd><br>
<dd>In the manner of a person, object, etc., quickly sliding down a slope.</dd><br>
<dd>3. quickly; in a scurry</dd><br>
<dd>재빠른 걸음으로 걷거나 따라다니는 모양.</dd><br>
<dd>In the manner of walking or following someone in quick steps.</dd><br>
<dd>4. neatly</dd><br>
<dd>여럿이 한 줄로 고르게 있는 모양.</dd><br>
<dd>In the manner of a group of people or objects being in a single, neat file.</dd><br>
<dt>쪼르르 [쪼르르]</dt><br>
<dd>1. quickly; in a trickle</dd><br>
<dd>가는 물줄기 등이 빠르게 흘러내리는 소리. 또는 그 모양.</dd><br>
<dd>A word used to describe the trickling sound made when a thin flow of water runs down, or such a motion.</dd><br>
<dd>2. quickly; in a sliding manner</dd><br>
<dd>작은 사람이나 물건 등이 기울어진 곳에서 빠르게 미끄러져 내리는 모양.</dd><br>
<dd>In the manner of a small person, object, etc., quickly sliding down a slope.</dd><br>
<dd>3. quickly; in a scurry</dd><br>
<dd>작고 재빠른 걸음으로 걷거나 따라다니는 모양.</dd><br>
<dd>In the manner of walking or following someone in small quick steps.</dd><br>
<dd>4. neatly</dd><br>
<dd>작은 것들이 한 줄로 고르게 있는 모양.</dd><br>
<dd>In the manner of a group of small people or objects being in a single, neat file.</dd><br>
<dt>주르르 [주르르]</dt><br>
<dd>1. quickly</dd><br>
<dd>굵은 물줄기 등이 빠르게 흘러내리는 소리. 또는 그 모양.</dd><br>
<dd>In such a manner that a thick flow of water runs down, or the sound made by such a flow.</dd><br>
<dd>2. quickly</dd><br>
<dd>사람이나 물건 등이 기울어진 곳에서 빠르게 미끄러져 내리는 모양.</dd><br>
<dd>In such a manner that a person, object, etc., quickly slides down a slope.</dd><br>
<dd>3. quickly</dd><br>
<dd>재빠른 걸음으로 걷거나 따라다니는 모양.</dd><br>
<dd>In a manner of walking or following someone in quick steps.</dd><br>
<dd>4. neatly</dd><br>
<dd>여럿이 한 줄로 고르게 있는 모양.</dd><br>
<dd>In a manner of a group of people or objects being in a single, neat file.</dd><br>
<dt>조촐히 [조촐히]</dt><br>
<dd>1. cozily</dd><br>
<dd>작지만 아담하고 깨끗이.</dd><br>
<dd>In a manner of being small but petite and clean.</dd><br>
<dd>2. demurely</dd><br>
<dd>행동이나 행실 등이 깔끔하고 얌전히.</dd><br>
<dd>In a manner of being refined and dignified in behavior or deed.</dd><br>
<dd>3. neatly; simply</dd><br>
<dd>외모나 모습 등이 깨끗하고 멋이 있게.</dd><br>
<dd>In a manner of being neat and classy in appearance or looks.</dd><br>
<dd>4. quietly; simply</dd><br>
<dd>조용하고 간단하게.</dd><br>
<dd>In a manner of being quiet and simple.</dd><br>
<dt>조르르 [조르르]</dt><br>
<dd>1. gently</dd><br>
<dd>가는 물줄기 등이 빠르게 흘러내리는 소리. 또는 그 모양.</dd><br>
<dd>In such a manner that a thin, narrow flow of water, etc., runs down, or the sound made by such a flow.</dd><br>
<dd>2. quickly</dd><br>
<dd>작은 사람이나 물건 등이 기울어진 곳에서 빠르게 미끄러져 내리는 모양.</dd><br>
<dd>In such a manner that a small person, object, etc., quickly slides down a slope.</dd><br>
<dd>3. quickly</dd><br>
<dd>작고 재빠른 걸음으로 걷거나 따라다니는 모양.</dd><br>
<dd>In a manner of walking or following someone in small quick steps.</dd><br>
<dd>4. neatly</dd><br>
<dd>작은 것들이 한 줄로 고르게 있는 모양.</dd><br>
<dd>In a manner of a group of small objects being in a single, neat file.</dd><br>
<dt>정연히 [정연히]</dt><br>
<dd>neatly</dd><br>
<dd>말이나 글, 행동 등이 앞뒤가 들어맞고 짜임새가 있게.</dd><br>
<dd>In a manner of speech, text, act, etc., being coherent and organized.</dd><br>
<dt>정결히 [정결히]</dt><br>
<dd>neatly; clean</dd><br>
<dd>깨끗하고 깔끔하게.</dd><br>
<dd>In a manner of being clean and organized.</dd><br>
<dt>정갈히 [정갈히]</dt><br>
<dd>neatly; clean</dd><br>
<dd>보기에 깨끗하고 깔끔하게.</dd><br>
<dd>In a manner of being clean and organized in appearance.</dd><br>
<dt>얌전히 [얌전히]</dt><br>
<dd>1. gently; meekly</dd><br>
<dd>성격이나 태도가 조용하고 차분하게.</dd><br>
<dd>With a quiet and calm personality or attitude.</dd><br>
<dd>2. neatly; cleanly; tidily</dd><br>
<dd>모양이 단정하고 반듯하게.</dd><br>
<dd>In a neat and tidy shape.</dd><br>
<dt>시원히 [시원히]</dt><br>
<dd>1. (no equivalent expression)</dd><br>
<dd>덥지도 춥지도 않고 적당하게 서늘하게.</dd><br>
<dd>In the state of being moderately cool, neither hot nor cold.</dd><br>
<dd>2. (no equivalent expression)</dd><br>
<dd>음식이 먹기 좋을 정도로 차고 산뜻하거나, 속이 후련할 정도로 뜨겁게.</dd><br>
<dd>In the state of food being cold and refreshing and thus being good to eat, or being hot enough to make one feel refreshed.</dd><br>
<dd>3. without interruptions</dd><br>
<dd>막힌 데가 없이 활짝 트여 마음이 답답하지 않게.</dd><br>
<dd>In the state of something not feeling confined because it has an open view without any obstructions.</dd><br>
<dd>4. without reserve</dd><br>
<dd>말이나 행동이 막힘이 없고 활발하게.</dd><br>
<dd>In the state of one's way of speaking or behaving being unhesitating and lively.</dd><br>
<dd>5. cleanly; neatly</dd><br>
<dd>지저분하던 것이 깨끗하고 말끔하게.</dd><br>
<dd>In the state of something that was dirty being clean and neat.</dd><br>
<dd>6. (no equivalent expression)</dd><br>
<dd>답답했던 마음이 풀려서 가뿐하고 후련하게.</dd><br>
<dd>In the state of feeling light and relieved because one's anxiety has been resolved.</dd><br>
<dd>7. (no equivalent expression)</dd><br>
<dd>가렵거나 속이 더부룩하던 느낌이 사라져 기분이 좋게.</dd><br>
<dd>In the state of feeling good because an itch or heaviness on the stomach has gone away.</dd><br>
<dt>시원스레 [시원스레]</dt><br>
<dd>1. (no equivalent expression)</dd><br>
<dd>덥지도 춥지도 않고 적당히 서늘하게.</dd><br>
<dd>In the state of being moderately cool, neither hot nor cold.</dd><br>
<dd>2. without interruptions</dd><br>
<dd>막힌 데가 없이 활짝 트여 마음이 답답하지 않게.</dd><br>
<dd>In the state of something not feeling confined because it has an open view without any obstructions.</dd><br>
<dd>3. without reserve</dd><br>
<dd>말이나 행동이 막힘이 없고 활발하게.</dd><br>
<dd>In the state of one's way of speaking or behaving being unhesitating and lively.</dd><br>
<dd>4. cleanly; neatly</dd><br>
<dd>지저분하던 것이 환하고 깨끗하게.</dd><br>
<dd>In the state of something dirty being cleaned neatly.</dd><br>
<dd>5. (no equivalent expression)</dd><br>
<dd>답답한 마음이 풀려서 가뿐하고 후련하게.</dd><br>
<dd>In the state of feeling light and relieved because one's anxiety has been resolved.</dd><br>
<dd>6. (no equivalent expression)</dd><br>
<dd>가렵거나 속이 더부룩하던 느낌이 사라져 기분이 좋을 정도로.</dd><br>
<dd>In the state of feeling good because an itch or heaviness on the stomach has gone away.</dd><br>
<dt>반듯반듯 [반듣빤듣]</dt><br>
<dd>1. straight</dd><br>
<dd>생김새가 비슷한 여러 개가 비뚤거나 굽거나 기울지 않고 바른 모양.</dd><br>
<dd>In a state in which several things of similar appearance are straight, not tilted, bent, or crooked.</dd><br>
<dd>2. neatly; evenly</dd><br>
<dd>생김새가 아주 고르고 말끔한 모양.</dd><br>
<dd>In the state of being even and neat.</dd><br>
<dt>말짱히 [말짱히]</dt><br>
<dd>1. spotlessly; impeccably; unhurt</dd><br>
<dd>흠이나 다친 곳 등이 없고 온전한 상태로.</dd><br>
<dd>In the state of being intact without flaws, wounds, etc.</dd><br>
<dd>2. sanely; soberly</dd><br>
<dd>정신이 맑고 또렷한 상태로.</dd><br>
<dd>In a state in which one's consciousness is clear and distinct.</dd><br>
<dd>3. neatly; immaculately</dd><br>
<dd>지저분한 것이 없고 말끔하고 깨끗한 상태로.</dd><br>
<dd>In the state of being tidy and clear without dirty things.</dd><br>
<dt>또박또박 [또박또박]</dt><br>
<dd>1. neatly; clearly</dd><br>
<dd>말이나 글씨 등이 분명하고 또렷한 모양.</dd><br>
<dd>In the manner that a remark or handwriting, etc., are clear and distinct.</dd><br>
<dd>2. regularly; punctually</dd><br>
<dd>규칙이나 차례 등을 한 번도 어기지 않고 지키는 모양.</dd><br>
<dd>In the manner of following a rule, order, etc., without violating it.</dd><br>
<dt>단정히 [단정히]</dt><br>
<dd>neatly; tidily</dd><br>
<dd>겉모습이 깔끔하거나 태도가 얌전하고 바르게.</dd><br>
<dd>In a clean appearance or in a quiet and proper manner.</dd><br>
<dt>깨끗이 [깨끄시]</dt><br>
<dd>1. clean</dd><br>
<dd>더럽지 않게.</dd><br>
<dd>Not dirtily.</dd><br>
<dd>2. clearly</dd><br>
<dd>빛깔 등이 흐리지 않고 맑게.</dd><br>
<dd>In the state of a color being clear, not vague.</dd><br>
<dd>3. neatly; tidily</dd><br>
<dd>가지런히 잘 정돈되고 단정하게.</dd><br>
<dd>In the state of being in good shape.</dd><br>
<dd>4. refreshingly</dd><br>
<dd>맛이나 느낌이 상쾌하고 개운하게.</dd><br>
<dd>In the state of tasting refreshing or feeling fine.</dd><br>
<dd>5. completely; clearly</dd><br>
<dd>남은 것이나 흔적이 없이.</dd><br>
<dd>Without leaving behind any leftovers or traces.</dd><br>
<dd>6. completely; flatly; frankly</dd><br>
<dd>어떤 일에 집착하거나 구차하게 매달리지 않고 마음에 섭섭함이나 불만이 없이.</dd><br>
<dd>Without clinging to something pathetically or without regrets or complaints.</dd><br>
<dd>7. completely; entirely</dd><br>
<dd>병을 앓고 난 뒤의 어떤 증상이나 힘든 일 뒤의 부작용 등이 없이.</dd><br>
<dd>Without any lingering symptoms or side effects after sickness or hardships.</dd><br>
<dd>8. fairly; honorably</dd><br>
<dd>마음씨나 행동이 떳떳하고 분명하며 올바르게.</dd><br>
<dd>In the manner of one's mind or behavior being honorable, clear, and right.</dd><br>
<dd>9. innocently</dd><br>
<dd>마음이나 표정이 사납거나 험하지 않고 순수하게.</dd><br>
<dd>In the state of one's mind or facial expression being pure, neither fierce nor violent.</dd><br>
</li>
</ul>